<head>
<title>The history of OEC</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="images/oeclgwm1.gif">
<p align=center><font color="#008000"><font size=5>OHIO ENVIRONMENTAL COUNCIL</font></font></p>
<p align=center><font color="#008000">400 Dublin Avenue &#183; Columbus, Ohio 43215-2333</font></p>
<p align=center><font color="#008000">Tel. (614) 224&#183;4900 &#183; Fax (614) 224-4914</font></p>
<p align=center><font color="#008000"><font size=4>OHIO ENVIRONMENTAL COUNCIL BACKGROUND</font></font></p>
<blockquote>
<p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>The Ohio Environmental Council (OEC) is a 501 (c) (3) non-profit organization founded 
in, 1969 to assist local environmental organizations across Ohio in promoting improved 
environmental quality in our state. Our 501 (c) (3 ) status was granted by the. U. S. 
Internal Revenue Service in 1972 and was reaffirmed on July 31, 1989.</font></font></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>As of Apri1 1996, we serve approximately 100 member organizations and over 450 
individual members statewide. The Council maintains a permanent office in Columbus, 
has four full-time staff, and has utilized the services of several interns during the past 
year. OEC's activities are over seen by a Board of Directors representing a broad cross- 
section of environmental interests from across the state. Our statewide effectiveness has 
grown dramatically in the past four years through our increase in membership. </font></font></p>
<p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>We maintain a comprehensive library of environmental, scientific, and governmental 
information in Columbus, distribute a newsletter to our membership and the media, 
closely monitor legislative and administrative actions of Ohio government, and conduct a 
media education campaign on Ohio's unique environmental issues. Funding for the 
Council consists of membership dues from our member individuals and organizations 
and from foundation grants. </font></font></p>
<p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>OEC accomplishments.in the past two years include:</font></font></p>
<ul>
<li><p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>developing a collaborative plan of action among state-wide and grass-roots 
environmental groups in Ohio to share resources and create.a stronger, more 
efficient, environmental movement in the state;</font></font> </p>
</li>
<li><p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>creating The Greenpages, a grass-roots directory and resource tool for Ohio 
citizens and agencies to access expertise within environmental organizations, 
universities, and government agencies;</font></font> </p>
</li>
<li><p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>developing a more efficient and comprehensive database to increase OEC's 
productivity and to more readily supply information to citizens;</font></font> </p>
</li>
<li><p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>collaborating with other agencies in planning and implementation of environmental 
justice projects;</font></font> </p>
</li>
<li><p align=left><font color="#008000"><font size=4>intervenor in the permitting process of WTI, a hazardous waste incinerator in East 
Liverpool, Ohio;</font></font> </p>
</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
</body>

</html>
