<html>

<head>
<title>Campaign For Energy Efficiency</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="images/oeclgwm1.gif">
<p><img src="images/oec_ceeg.jpg" align=bottom width=392 height=178></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><font size=4>&#160;</font><font color="#008000"><font size=5>The goal of the Campaign for an Energy Efficient Ohio (CEEO) is to create 
the regulatory, policy, legislative, and public awareness necessary for Ohio to 
make the transition to a sustainable energy future.</font></font></p>
<p><font color="#008000"><font size=4>&#160;A sustainable energy future is one in which we have:</font></font></p>
<ul>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>maximized the use of energy efficiency to reduce energy use;</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>maximized the use of renewable energy supply technologies as alternatives to nuclear and fossil 
fuel energy supply;</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>reduced to a minimum the environmental impacts of energy production and use; and</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>integrated energy and environmental concerns with broader societal goals, namely; equity, 
health, econimic development and quality of life.</font></font></li>
</ul>
<p><font color="#008000"><font size=4>The Campaign proposes to implement &quot;The Agenda&quot; through the following on-going efforts:</font></font></p>
<ul>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>education of the public, press, energy consumers, and policy-makers on impacts of energy use 
on environmental, health, and economy</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>promotion of energy efficiency and renewable technologies to industrial, commercial, 
institutional, and residential consumers;</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>expansion, mobilization, and maintenance of a strong, diverse coalition of representatives from 
many membership organizations willing to be advocates for sustainable energy;</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>research and analysis on the benefits of sustainable energy, the negative impacts of our 
dependence on fossil and nuclear fuels, and the most appropriate mechanisms for 
implementation in Ohio;</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>advocacy for effective policies and programs and against policies that undercut sustainability;</font></font></li>
<li><font color="#0000FF"><font size=4>development of a resource and referral center to help Ohioans get information they require to 
become energy efficient.</font></font></li>
</ul>
</body>

</html>
</DOC>
