<head>
<title>GreenData Home Page</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#C5D0B0">
<h1 align=center>Green Data</h1>
<h4 align=center><em>Databases for researching environmental topics</em></h4>
<p>Many of the following data bases are for use by industry, but we are including them so that <strong>all 
</strong>shareholders in environmental issues will have access to the same information. We have chosen 
some that we feel are relevant to current issues today. You might also check our <a href="http://www.greenlink.org/links.html">GreenLinks</a> page 
for other Internet Links.</p>
<p><u>Descriptions:</u></p>
<p><a href="http://www.vote-smart.org/"><strong>Vote Smart</strong></a><strong> -</strong> A compilation of political information about both issues and candidates for the 
upcoming election. It is organized on state and national levels.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.clay.net"><strong>Environmental Professional's Home Page</strong></a><strong> -</strong> A useful link to information from many government 
agencies. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.rtk.net"><strong>RTK NET </strong></a>- listings of all pollutants produced by companies in your area plus other very useful 
information. Click on &quot;View list of Databases&quot; and then on &quot;search software&quot; to get to the 
information you need.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.crp.org"><strong>Center for Responsive Politics </strong></a>- discover the sources of campaign funds and other timely 
political information.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.thompson.com/tpg/enviro/pack/packstates.html"><strong>Thompson Publishing</strong></a><strong>:</strong> a good list of pending environmental legislation for several states: </p>
<p><a href="http://www.osha.gov"><strong>OSHA Home Page </strong></a>- Information on standards for many chemicals and also the latest on 
regulations. Other useful information is also available.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.epa.gov"><strong>U.S. EPA Home Page </strong></a>- updates, listing of hazardous waste sites, newletters, and data for 19 
chemicals.</p>
<p><a href="http://odin.chemistry.uakron.edu"><strong>Hazardous Chemical Database</strong></a> - Choose Hazardous Chemical Database when you reach the 
page. You will need to type in the whole name, not an initial.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h5>Return to: <a href="http://www.greenlink.org/">Greenlink<tt>TM</tt> Home Page</a> </h5>
<h5><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/signup.html">Sign up</a> for a <b><blink>FREE</blink></b> Charter Membership in GreenLink:</h5>
<h5>For more information about Greenlink, send e-mail to: <a href="mailto:info@greenlink.org">info@greenlink.org</a></h5>
<h5>Visit our Network Service Provider: <a href="http://www.webframe.com/">WebFrame.com </a></h5>
