<head>
<title>Brownfields</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h1 align=center><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/images/glnklogo.gif"><img src="glnklogo.gif" alt="GreenLink: wired for the environment." align=top border=0></a> <br>
<strong>Brownfields Issues</strong> </h1>
<hr>
<p><a href="#Ohio EPA recently filed"><strong>Brownfields Lobby moves to Rule Committee</strong></a><strong> (includes full text of JCARR procedures, 
Posted Nov 10,1996)</strong></p>
<p><a href="#Ohio EPA "><strong>Brownfields Postponed: </strong></a><strong>Citizen's Release (from Nancy Whetstone, Ohio EPA)</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/rule1pdf.html"><strong>Brownfields Rule Summary Documents</strong></a><strong> (As of Oct 03, 1996)</strong></p>
<hr>
<ul>
<li><a href="#Forums">Forums</a> </li>
<li><a href="#Environmental Organizations Facts and Figures">Environmental Organizations Facts and Figures</a></li>
<li><a href="#Contacts for Regulatory Agencies and Advocacy Groups">Contacts for Regulatory Agents and Advocacy Groups</a></li>
<li><a href="#Internal Ohio EPA and Other Documents relating to Brownfields">Internal Ohio EPA and Other Documents Relating to Brownfields</a><hr>
<h3><a name="Forums">Forums</a> </h3>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/forum/REG-AGENCIES/">Regulatory Agency Forum </a>(<strong>The forums are available to all GreenLink members.</strong> If you 
are not a GreenLink member, please <a href="http://www.greenlink.org/signup.html">Sign up</a> now. It's free!<hr>
<h3><a name="Environmental Organizations Facts and Figures">Environmental Organizations Facts and Figures</a> </h3>
</li>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/cit_day1.html">OEPA Puts Public Health And Groundwater at Risk </a>( <strong>Ohio Citizens Action</strong>, Jane Forest 
Dayton/Cincinnati Area)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/oec1.html">Oppose New Brownfields Rules</a> (<strong>Ohio Environmental Council</strong>)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/sierra1.html">Brownfields Guidance Document </a>(<strong>Sierra Club</strong> - presented by Jeff Skelding, Program 
Coordinator for Ohio)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/gec_vap.html">Greene Environmental Coalition Comments on Brownfields</a> (<strong>Bob Fisher and Tracy 
Slayton</strong></li>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/citdov1.html">How Clean is Clean </a>(Citizen Action - presented by Laura Yeomans, Research Director) 
<em>This document is scanned and may contain typographical errors. An image copy can be 
obtained from the </em><em><u>Internal Ohio EPA and Other Documents Relating to Brownfields</u></em><em> 
link on this page.</em></li>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/citdov2.html">Chemicals may pollute groundwater </a>(Citizen Action - presented by Laura Yeomans, 
Research Director) <em>This document is scanned and may contain typographical errors. An 
image copy can be obtained from the </em><em><u>Internal Ohio EPA and Other Documents 
Relating to Brownfields link on this page.</u></em><hr>
<h3><a name="Contacts for Regulatory Agencies and Advocacy Groups">Contacts for Regulatory Agencies and Advocacy Groups</a> </h3>
<p><a href="http://www.epa.ohio.gov/derr/volunt.html">OEPA Brownfields Contact</a> </p>
<h3><a name="Internal Ohio EPA and Other Documents relating to Brownfields">Internal Ohio EPA and Other Documents Relating to Brownfields</a> </h3>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/oepapdf.html">Internal Ohio EPA Documents Relating to Brownfields</a>. (Adobe Portable Document Format 
(PDF) files. Download and print these documents in their original form.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/brownpdf.html">Other Documents Relating to Brownfields</a>. (Adobe Portable Document Format (PDF) files. 
Download and print these documents in their original form.</li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<p><a name="Ohio EPA ">Ohio EPA </a>has decided to extend the public comment period on the proposed Voluntary Action 
Program (brownfields) rules until <strong>Oct. 10, 1996</strong>. The extension was granted in response to several 
requests from representatives of industry and environmental interest groups.</p>
<p>The proposed rules will be refiled with the legislature's rule review committee(JCARR) by early 
October, enabling the rules to be on JCARR's <strong>October 22 </strong>agenda.</p>
<hr>
<p><a name="Ohio EPA recently filed">Ohio EPA recently filed</a> a final set of Brownfields rules with the Joint Committee on Agency Rule 
Review (JCARR) on October 31. JCARR is a bi-partisin committee with members from the House 
and the Senate. The members are charged with ensuring that the rules proposed by state agencies 
meet certain statutory requirements, strictly limited to the following:</p>
<p>1)	The agency proposing the rules has the <strong>statutory authority</strong> to make the rules;</p>
<p>2)	The rule is not in conflict witht he <strong>intent of the legislature;</strong></p>
<p>3) The rule is not in <strong>conflict with another rule</strong>;</p>
<p>4) The agency proposing the rule has<strong> proposed a proper rule summary and fiscal analysis.</strong></p>
<p><em><strong>The above is the only criteria the committe may consider in its deliberations. Testimony at 
the JCARR hearing must be limited to these topics. </strong></em></p>
<p>JCARR's jurisdiction ends on November 29th. It is assumed these rules will be heard at the 
November 19th meeting, 30 days later than earlier reports. </p>
<ol>
<li>JCARR's <a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/members.html">Members</a></li>
<li>JCARR's <a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/reasons.html">Criteria</a></li>
<li>JCARR's <a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/jcarr.html">&quot;Internal Operations Guidebook&quot;</a> </li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h5>Return to:<a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/index.html"> Brownfields Home Page</a></h5>
<h5>Return to: <a href="http://www.greenlink.org/">Greenlink<tt>TM</tt> Home Page</a> </h5>
