alt="Rivers Unlimited"></h1>

<hr>

<h1 align="center"><i>C.A.N.O.E.</i></h1>

<p align="center"><font size="4"><b><i>Citizens Activist Network
for the Ohio Environment'</i></b></font></p>

<p align="center"><a href="mailto:riveruoh@aol.com">E- mail:
riveruoh@aol.com </a></p>

<hr>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/11597.html">Notice</a>
of <strong>citizen&#146;s training conference</strong> entitled <strong>Conserving
Ohio&#146;s Rivers and Wetlands</strong> on January 26-28.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/121896.html">Week
of 12/18/96</a> : It's Not a Precedent, It's a Policy!!,
Conserving Ohio's Rivers and Wetlands: Citizen Training
Conference, Starting Up: A Handbook for New River and Watershed
Organizations, Save Money and Support the Work of RU at the Same
Time</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/dirct.html">New
RU Director Named</a></p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/wisriv.html">New
Wisconsin Rivers Site</a></p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/121296.html">Week
of 12/12/96</a>, Twinsburg City Council Opposes Plan to Move
Tinker's Creek, Governor Signs Polluter's Protection Act, State
Takes Action to Remove Dam on Little Miami River, Save Money and
Support RU at the Same Time</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/book.html">Suggested
Book Title</a>: &quot;Starting Up: A Handbook for New River and
Watershed Organizations&quot; </p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/121096.html">Week
of 12/10/96</a> , Rivers Unlimited Welcomes a New Staff Member;
Fish May be in the Future of Cuyahoga River; Greenways, Rivers,
Fish May get Additional Protection From Index Developed for
Riparian Corridor Study; Save Money and Support the Work of RU at
the Same Time</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/spec.html">Special
Alert - Nov. 26, 1996</a></p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/111896.html">Week
of 11/18/96</a>, Environment Wins Half a Loaf in Legislature, The
Economics of River Protection, Rivers Unlimited Holds Annual
Meeting This Weekend.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/111196.html">Week
of 11/11/96</a>, Decision to Move Tinker's Creek Appealed, RU
Asks Ohio EPA to Eliminate Limited Resource Waters, Save Money
and Support the Work of RU at the Same Time</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/11496.html">Week
of 11/04/96</a>, Paddlers and Pedestrians to Gather in Cleveland
for Clean Water, President Signs Bill Protecing Nation's
Waterways, Barberton Adds $3.5 Million To Develop National
Heritage Corridor</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/102896.html">Week
of 10/28/96</a>, Columbus Citizens Give Input on Riverfront
Development, Statewide Greenways Initiative Receives Funding
Boost, Pulp and Paper Mill Continuing Source of Controversy</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/101596.html">Week
of 10/15/96</a>, River's Annual Awards, OEPA Favors Parking Lot
Over Waterway</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/101196.html">Week
of 10/11/96</a>, State Turns Its Back on Clean Waters</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/100296.html">Week
of 10/02/96,</a> Buckeye Forest Council, Cleveland Bikeway,
ISTEA, Hike/Bike Path Use, Greenway Plan.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/092396.html"
target="canoe 092396">Week of 09/23/96</a>, Ohio Wetlands,
Southeastern Ohio Streams Restoration, National Rivers Policy Act</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/091896.html">Week
of 09/20/96 </a>, Ohio Takings Bill, Ohio Wetlands, Meeting
announcements</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/081496.html">Week
of 08/14/96</a> , Yellowstone Averts Mining, Hocking River
Problem, Section 401</p>

<p><a href="http://www.greenlink.org/rivers/canoe/073096.html">Week
of 07/30/96</a> , Ohio Anti-Degredation Rules</p>

