<h1 align=center>Internal Ohio EPA Documents</h1>
<h3 align=center>All documents presented on these pages are available through the 
public records laws under the Freedom of Information Act. </h3>
<hr>
<p><a href="#Ohio EPA Internal Documents">Ohio EPA Internal Documents </a></p>
<hr>
<p>These pages are presented in Adobe Portable Document Format (PDF). You must have 
Adobe Reader installed on your computer to view these documents. Download the free 
Adobe Reader, <a href="ftp://ftp.greenlink.org/public-ftp/adobe/acroread.mac">Macintosh Version </a>(2.6 Mbytes),<a href="ftp://ftp.greenlink.org/public-ftp/adobe/acroread.exe"> Windows Version </a>(1.5 Mbytes) from 
our server. For other operating systems download software for free direct from Adobe at 
<a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/readstep.html">www.adobe.com</a>. With Adobe reader you can print or view the documents in their original 
form. You may use the document just as if we mailed you a photocopy.</p>
<p>After installing the Adobe Reader, you will be able to view and print the downloaded files.</p>
<p>Remember Adobe PDF files are images, equivalent to photocopies of the original 
documents. It may take a few moments to download. </p>
<hr>
<h3 align=center><a name="Ohio EPA Internal Documents"><strong>Ohio EPA Internal Documents</strong></a></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.greenlink.org/greenlink/brown/memo819.pdf">Memo to Jan Carlson, Chief DERR and Others at Ohio EPA</a> (<strong>15K</strong>) This August 
19, 1996 memo points out several technical deficiencies in the proposed Brownfield 
Rules. </li>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.greenlink.org/greenlink/brown/memplum1.pdf">Memo to Mark Sheahan, Supervisor DERR Ohio EPA</a> (<strong>252K</strong>) This March 27, 
1996 memo titled <strong>Plume Lengths</strong> clearly details existing groundwater 
contamination that could be exempt if the proposed Brownfield Rules. </li>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.greenlink.org/greenlink/brown/smin1.pdf">Memo to Maria Galanti, DERR Ohio EPA</a> (<strong>140K</strong>) This undated memo outlines a 
number of concerns about the proposed Brownfield Rules. The original we worked 
from had been marked up with a highlighter - some lines are not readable.</li>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.greenlink.org/greenlink/brown/memo896.pdf">Memo to Jan Carlson, Chief DERR Ohio EPA</a> (<strong>297K</strong>) This August 16, 1996 memo 
outlines serious deficiencies in the proposed Brownfield Rules. The original we 
worked from was a faint fax, but readable.</li>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.greenlink.org/greenlink/brown/memoall.pdf">Memo to Donald Schregardus, Director of Ohio EPA (</a><strong>272K</strong>) This Jan 1, 1996 
memo includes 7 pages of signatures from Ohio EPA Staff. (Note this memo refers 
to the first draft of the proposed Brownfield Rules; some items mentioned have been 
addressed in the current version).</li>
</ul>
