<b>From:</b> <a href="mailto:gec@sprynet.com">gec@sprynet.com</a><br>
<b>Date:</b> Wed, 16 Oct 96 11:29:22 -0500<br>
<b>To:</b> <a href="mailto:reg-agencies@greenlink.org">reg-agencies@greenlink.org</a><br>
<b>Subject:</b> GEC comments on Brownfields rules submitted 10/15/96<br>
<hr>
<pre>
Date: October 14, 1996

To: Voluntary Action Program
    Division of Emergency Response and Remediation
    Ohio Environmental Protection Agency

Fr: Greene Environmental Coalition
    Box 266 
    Yellow Springs, OH 45387
    513-767-2109

Re: Additional Comments 

	The Greene Environmental Coalition reiterates its support for  
reasonable incentives that may encourage the clean-up and development of 
so-called Brownfields properties in Ohio.  However, review of the proposed rules 
released on October 3 leaves us with ongoing concern about both the rules and 
the process for embracing the public.  

	With only one exception, none of the comments we submitted at the public 
hearing in Dayton on September 5 have been addressed in this proposed rule 
package.  In 3745-300-10 (E) (1) (iii) the agency clarified the area served by a 
community water system.  Thank you for recognizing the need for clarity.  
Although we did not comment on the issue of flow rates, the agency strengthened 
3745-300-10 (C) (2) (b) (ii).  Again, thank you.  

	It does not appear that our comments, and apparently others who 
commented during the early September public hearings, were not given serious 
consideration.  Therefore, we must assume that the next version of rules will 
address these concerns and the concerns of the many other citizens that 
testified during the public hearing process.   

While some are suggesting that the Agency does not have the time nor the 
personnel to address the concerns of the many Ohioans who commented on these 
rules, we must believe the Agency will not yield, and will aggressively pursue 
its charter to provide for the protection of the public health and environment. 
 Knowing you will give serious consideration to the carefully researched 
comments received during the last 45 days, we look forward to seeing a rule 
package that we can support to the members of the JCARR.  

Thank you again for the opportunity to comment.  

Bruce Cornett for the Greene Environmental Coalition.  
 



</pre>
