<b>Subject:</b> Brownfields<br>
<hr>
<pre>
Alert Alert Alert Alert Alert Alert Alert Alert Alert Alert 

A memo dated October 3, 1996 (and received today, October 11, 
1996) from Ohio EPA extends the Brownfields Rules public 
comment period until Tuesday, October 15th.  Ohio EPA 
suggests that they will file the latest version of the rules 
with JCARR on October 23 or 24.  

The package from Ohio EPA contained the latest version of the
proposed rules, including summary pages outlining changes 
from the July, 1996 version.  In addition, the rules contain 
strike-out and red-lined text to show the sections changed.  

Each of the rule summary pages includes references to changes 
made as a result of public comments taken through the month 
of September, 1996.  Unfortunately, the package does not 
contain a responsiveness summary detailing OEPA's response to 
issues posed by the public.  It is important to remember that 
some of the persons commenting were not environmental 
advocates.

We have not performed an analysis of the changes as yet.  
Cursory review and newspaper accounts lead us to believe that 
many of the issues concerning the advocacy community have not 
been adequately addressed.  

It does not appear that the changes to the rules have been 
posted on the EPA Web site.  We will attempt to get the 
summary pages scanned and posted to  
<a href="http://www.greenlink.org/brown/index.html">http://www.greenlink.org/brown/index.html</a>
before the weekend is over. We will also post details about 
the JCARR rule acceptance process next week.    

If you have not received a copy of the rules, call OEPA at
(614)644.2292 or e-mail Jenifer Kwasniewski at
jenifer_kwasniewski@central.epa.ohio.gov

If you have comments please post them to the legislative 
forum on GreenLink.  

Bruce Cornett for the Greene Environmental Coalition
</pre>
