<CENTER>
<H2>Reactors Within the Midwest Compact:</H2>
</CENTER>
<P> <BR>
 </P>
<PRE>
                                                Opened               30 Years*
Davis-Besse   (OH)                              1977                    2007
Perry Unit 1   (OH)                             1987                    2017
Perry Unit 2   (OH)                             1995                    2025

LaCrosse        (WI)                            1969                    Shut Down
Point Beach Unit 1 (WI)                         1970                    2000
Point Beach Unit 2 (WI)                         1972                    2002
Kewaunee (WI)                                   1974                    2004

Monticello (MN)                                 1971                    2001
Prairie Island Unit I (MN)                      1973                    2003
Prairie Island Unit 2 (MN)                      1974                    2004

Duane Arnold (IA)                               1975                    2005
Callaway (MO)                                   1982                    2012    
                        
</PRE>
<HR>
<P>*Yankee Rowe (MA) operated for 28 years. The average
shut-down date for U.S. reactors thus far comes after less
than 20 years of operation.</P>
<HR>
<P><B>Reactors within the Midwest Compact</B>: Reacotrs
with operating and maitenance costs higher than the cost of
buying replacement power --<BR>
 </P>
