<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>Canoe-Waters conference</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p>Take advantage of an exciting opportunity to learn ways to
better protect the waterways of Ohio!!!</p>

<p>The Great Lakes Regional Office of the National Audubon
Society and Rivers Unlimited are sponsoring a <strong>citizen&#146;s
training conference</strong> entitled <strong>Conserving
Ohio&#146;s Rivers and Wetlands</strong> on January 26-28 at the
Courtyard Mariott, 35W. Spring St., Columbus, Ohio. The
conference runs from 6:00pm to 10:00pm on Sunday, January 26,
7:30am to 9:00pm on Monday January 27th, and from 7:30am to
4:00pm on January 28.</p>

<p>If you are interested in gaining skills to help protect clean
waters and healthy rivers in Ohio this is the conference for you!
You will have the chance to receive in-depth training in
wetlands, scenic rivers and/or takings. Additionally, you will
learn how to effectively use the media, how the legislative
process works, and how to influence the legislature and state
agencies. Sunday&#146;s reception, Monday and Tuesday&#146;s
breakfast buffets, Monday&#146;s lunch and all materials are
included. This 2 day seminar is available at the extremely low
price of $25 if you register before January 13rd. It is the
expectation of the sponsors that participants will attend the
entire conference. </p>

<p>For more information or a copy of the conference brochure
please the National Audubon Society - Great Lakes Regional Office
at (614) 224-3303 or contact Rivers Unlimited at (614) 487-7511. </p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

