<title>Affinity - Mustard Seed Market & Cafe Expand</title>
</head>

<body>

<h2 align="center"><font size="2">Mustard Seed Market &amp; Cafe
Expand</font></h2>

<p><font size="2">Months of anticipation will soon be over when a
locally owned business becomes one of the largest natural food
stores in the nation. Long recognized as one of the best natural
food retailers in the country, Mustard Seed Market &amp; Cafe has
now expanded by 3 1/2 times its previous size.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">&quot;Our growth has been so incredible that we
reached the point where our customers virtually demanded that we
expand,&quot; says Phillip Nabors, who co-owns the store with his
wife, Margaret. &quot;When we started this business, we could not
find many items that met our standards, now we offer an entire
supermarket full of them. It&#146;s a celebration of
purity,&quot; said Margaret Nabors.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">And Mustard Seed&#146;s standards are strict
indeed. All foods sold in the store and served in the Cafe are
free from unwanted food additives. They are free from unwanted
chemical additives, harmful chemical preservatives, artificial
flavorings and colorings, growth hormones (meat and poultry),
animal testing, saccharin or aspartame and irradiation.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Of course, all the special products and
services that have made Mustard Seed market so popular are still
there, only more so. There is an even larger selection of
organically grown produce, in fact, it&#146;s Ohio&#146;s
largest. There is a complete juice bar serving both fruit and
vegetable juices. The meat department where all meats are
naturally raised and free of growth hormones, has also been
expanded. There is also a fascinating selection of organic wines.
There are more natural health care products and other
health-oriented goods than ever before.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Not only will customers benefit, but so do
local and organic farmers. One of the store&#146;s primary
philosophies is the support of sustainable agriculture. Organic
farming is the most familiar form of sustainable agriculture. It
includes such practices as crop rotation, organic fertilization
and biological pest control. This form of farming is considered
&quot;sustainable&quot; because it can be practiced continuously
without causing damage to the environment.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Now that the current expansion is complete, the
store is now the largest natural-foods retailer in the state of
Ohio. In fact, it is matched by only a few stores in the entire
United States. For more nformation call Margaret Nabors at (330)
666-7333.</font></p>

<hr>

